<%# Phase 16 §3 — Unread badge fragment. Rendered next to the
    `notifications` nav link AND broadcast in place via Turbo Stream
    on every `Notification.after_create_commit` /
    `after_update_commit` (read-state flip). The wrapper element
    carries the stable `dom_id "notifications_badge"` Turbo Stream
    targets — the wrapper renders even at zero so a flip from
    1 → 0 swaps `1` for an empty container in place (no
    DOM-disappear).

    UX restructure 2026-05-10: the count is rendered as a superscript
    next to `[notifications]` in the nav, with NO surrounding brackets.
    Previous shape was `[notifications][ N ]`; current shape is
    `[notifications]<sup>N</sup>`. When `unread_count == 0` the `<sup>`
    is omitted entirely so layout collapses to just `[notifications]`. %>
<span id="notifications_badge" class="notifications-badge">
  <% if unread_count.to_i > 0 %>
    <sup class="notifications-badge-count" aria-label="<%= unread_count %> unread notifications"><%= unread_count %></sup>
  <% end %>
</span>
